  plantName: Chicory Flower
  description: Chicory (Cichorium intybus) is a hardy, perennial herbaceous plant
    in the dandelion family, known for its vibrant, lavender-blue flowers that line
    roadsides and meadows. It features a tough, wiry stem (up to 1.5m tall), milky
    sap, and blooms that typically open in the morning and close by afternoon.
